         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">15/11/61 ¶ Dear Mr Ligar. ¶  ¶ Mr Hopwood has on very heavy private expense explored the country towards Coopers Creek for pastoral purposes, but communicated in several letters ¶  ¶ unasked ¶  ¶ as a...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">61.11.15a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Charles Ligar</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">MS 13071 Royal Society of Victoria Exploration Committee records, box 2078/2, La Trobe Australian Manuscripts Collection, State Library of Victoria, Melbourne<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS black-edged.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M's sister, Bertha Doughty, died on 7 September 1861.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                  </p>
               </note>15/11/61</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Mr Ligar.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mr Hopwood has on very heavy private expense explored the country towards Coopers Creek for pastoral purposes, but communicated in several letters<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">unasked</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>as a friend<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">secretly</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to me the results,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letters not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>not having as yet legal possession of his new runs, altho' I am in no way but geographically interested in the matter.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The wish to communicate with him at all did<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">not</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">arise with me</hi>
               </seg>.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I think under the circumstances, whilst reluctantly responding to the request of a committee member to serve Mr Howitt with the intelligence, I acted as straight forward as I could, unless I wished to betray the confidence of a friend.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See also C. Ligar to M, 15 November 1861.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by Ligar, 18 November 1861: 'Mr Dickson | Place this letter with Dr Muellers telegram'.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M.s telegram has not been found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
